body:
I don't know where to best report this issue, so I try here.

Dependencies:
```toml
[dependencies]
diesel = { version = "1.4.4", features = ["postgres", "r2d2"] }
actix-rt = "1.1"
```


Code:
```rust
use diesel::{
    pg::PgConnection,
    r2d2::{ConnectionManager, Pool, PoolError, PooledConnection},
};
use std::time::Duration;

type PgPool = Pool<ConnectionManager<PgConnection>>;
pub type Connection = PooledConnection<ConnectionManager<PgConnection>>;

pub fn establish_connection() -> std::result::Result<PgPool, PoolError> {
    let database_url = "postgres://username:@localhost".to_string();
    let db_timeout = Duration::new(2, 0);

    let manager = ConnectionManager::<PgConnection>::new(database_url);
    Pool::builder()
        .connection_timeout(db_timeout)
        .build(manager)
}

#[actix_rt::test]
pub async fn test_establish_connection() {
    for _ in 0..20 {
        std::thread::spawn(move || {
            establish_connection().unwrap();
            Ok::<(), ()>(())
        });
    }
}
```

First you have to run postgres:
```
docker run -p 5432:5432 -e POSTGRES_USER=username -e POSTGRES_HOST_AUTH_METHOD=trust postgres
```
Then
```
cargo test
```

Output (not always but most of the time):
```
running 1 test
test test_establish_connection ... ok

test result: ok. 1 passed; 0 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out

k5_mutex_lock: Received error 22 (Invalid argument)
abc-000f8ad9d0bf24ba: ../../../include/k5-thread.h:376: k5_mutex_lock: Assertion `r == 0' failed.
k5_mutex_lock: Received error 22 (Invalid argument)
abc-000f8ad9d0bf24ba: ../../../include/k5-thread.h:376: k5_mutex_lock: Assertion `r == 0' failed.
k5_mutex_lock: Received error 22 (Invalid argument)
abc-000f8ad9d0bf24ba: ../../../include/k5-thread.h:376: k5_mutex_lock: Assertion `r == 0' failed.
k5_mutex_lock: Received error 22 (Invalid argument)
abc-000f8ad9d0bf24ba: ../../../include/k5-thread.h:376: k5_mutex_lock: Assertion `r == 0' failed.
error: test failed, to rerun pass '--lib'

Caused by:
  process didn't exit successfully: `/tmp/abc/target/debug/deps/abc-000f8ad9d0bf24ba` (signal: 6, SIGABRT: process abort signal)
```

It seems like these weird k5 errors go away when I actually join the threads I create, at which time I see that there are actually errors from postgres saying `FATAL:  sorry, too many clients already`.

Anyway, even when not joining the threads, I would not expect such obscure errors. Googling it gave me no results.
Btw, I am aware that it is bad to create threads in an async function.
